claims:
Claims 1. A method of research and development, the method comprising the steps of: transmitting a research project to a plurality of analyzers; receiving, from said plurality of analyzers, data relating to the research project; computing the hash of said data; recording on a blockchain said computed hash of the data; recording on a blockchain the transfer of a utility credit to each of the analyzers; selecting at least one best performing analyzer, based on the data relating to the research project received from that analyzer; recording on a blockchain the transfer of an interest credit to the at least one best performing analyzers; storing the data from the analyzers; receiving a request from a party to access the data, verifying that said party has recorded a transfer of a utility credit or interest credit on a blockchain; and transmitting the data to the party. 2. The method of claim 1 , wherein the step of transmitting the research project to a plurality of analyzers comprises transmitting the research task to a task pool, wherein the task pool is adapted to allow analyzers to receive a list of research tasks upon request, and to receive the research task upon request. 3. The method of claim 1, wherein the step of selecting at least one best performing analyzer comprises comparing the data received from each analyzer to the data received from one or more other analyzers. 4. The method of claim 1 , further including the step of transmitting an executed legal document. 5. The method of claim 4, wherein the step of transmitting an executed legal document comprises computing a cryptographic hash of the executed legal document and storing the cryptographic hash on a blockchain. 6. The method of claim 1 , wherein the step of receiving a request from a party to access the data comprises receiving an access request including a public key with which to encrypt the data, and wherein the step of transmitting to the party the data comprises encrypting the data with the public key before transmitting it. 7. The method of claim 6, wherein the step of transmitting the party the data further comprises uploading the encrypted data to a cloud storage system. 8. The method of claim 1, wherein the research task relates to a drug that is under development. 9. A system for research and development, comprising: a research and development stage management system, adapted to: transmit a research project to a plurality of analyzers; receive, from said plurality of analyzers, data relating to the research project; compute the hash of said data; 

 record on a blockchain the transfer of a utility credit to each of the analyzers; select at least one best performing analyzer, based on the data relating to the research project received from that analyzer; record on a blockchain the transfer of an interest credit to the at least one best performing analyzers; and store the data from the analyzers on a data access system, wherein the data access system is adapted to: receive a request to access the data from a party, verify that said party has recorded a transfer of a utility credit or interest credit on a blockchain; and transmit the data to the party. 10. The system of claim 9, wherein the research and development stage management systems implemented using a smart contract, the state of which is tracked using a blockchain. 11. The system of claim 9, further comprising: a task pool system, adapted to facilitate the transmittal of the research task to the at least one analyzer by the research and development stage management system, and adapted to: receive, from the research and development stage management system, the research task, store the research task in a memory, 

 receive, from the at least one analyzer a request, transmit, to the at least one analyzer, a response to the request selected from the group comprising: a list of research tasks stored in the memory, information about one or more research tasks stored in the memory, and one or more research tasks. 12. The system of claim 9, further comprising a judging system, adapted to facilitate the selection of at least one winning analyzer by the research and development stage management system, by comparing the data received from each analyzer to the data received from one or more other analyzers. 13. The system of claim 9, wherein the research and development stage management system is further adapted to receive an executed legal document. 14. The system of claim 14, wherein the research and development stage management system is further adapted to compute a cryptographic hash of the executed legal document, and store that hash on a blockchain. 15. The system of claim 9, wherein the data access management is further adapted to receive, from a party, a public key; encrypt the data using the public key; and transmit the encrypted data instead of the data to the party.
